UPDATE events SET description = '<p>This three-hour session features a live model and offers artists of all levels the opportunity to explore the human form through drawing.<br>
Figure Drawing Session: Timeless Bodies<br>
Date: Sunday, December 7, 2025<br>
Time: 3:00–6:00 PM<br>
Location: Oliva Gallery, 3618 W. Armitage Ave., Chicago, IL 60647<br>
<a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/figure-drawing-session-timeless-bodies-tickets-1757999015379?aff=erelpanelorg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Entry: $20, advance registration required</a></p>
<p>Oliva Gallery invites you to a special Figure Drawing Session held in conjunction with the First Annual Midwest Ceramic Exhibition: Timeless Bodies. This three-hour session features a live model and offers artists of all levels the opportunity to explore the human form through drawing.</p>
<p>The event complements the exhibition’s central theme of the body as a vessel of memory, resilience, and expression. Participants are encouraged to bring their own drawing materials. Easels and chairs will be provided.</p>
<p>About the Exhibition<br>
Timeless Bodies runs from November 7 through December 13, 2025, and features ceramic artists from across the Midwest. Curated by Chicago-based ceramicist Nancy Pirri, the exhibition presents a dynamic range of figurative and abstract ceramic works exploring the enduring power of the human form.</p>
<p>Contact:<br>
Oliva Gallery<br>
Email: olivagallery@gmail.com<br>
Phone: (847) 922-5736</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
 <p>
 <a>Official Website</a>
 </p>' WHERE id = '6367ea08-5d06-41f6-a656-e7988e895adf';
UPDATE events SET description = '<p>An annual exhibition of CAPE’s in-school Artist/Researcher Partners Program that brings together the artworks and investigations of over 1,600 students from 23 Chicago public schools. Convergence opens the world of classroom learning to viewers, highlighting how students conceptualize the world and academic material through creation.</p>
<p>Join us for the opening reception on May 9 from 11 AM–2 PM in the CAPE gallery. Enjoy light bites and refreshments while meeting the artists, students, and teachers behind this incredible work!</p>
 <p>
 <a>Official Website</a>
