UPDATE events SET description = '<p>Fulton Street Collective presents the closing night of our current installation SWIPE LEFT on Friday February 27th, from 6:30pm-9:30pm.</p>
<p>In an era of infinite choice, how do we process the finite sting of a broken heart?<br>
&#8220;Swipe Left&#8221; explores the intersection of traditional romantic grief and the unique digital fatigue of modern-day dating. From the &#8220;ghosting&#8221; of the digital age to the timeless ache of a long-term parting, this exhibition seeks to map the landscape of heartbreak in 2026. We are looking for work that investigates the vulnerability, chaos, and eventual resilience found in the aftermath of love. Whether your work deals with the &#8220;disposable&#8221; nature of app culture or the heavy, analog weight of a fractured soul, we want to see how you translate rejection into art.</p>
<p>Curated by Jude Lo</p>
<p><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/1983727797242" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RESERVATIONS RECOMMENDED: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/1983727797242</a><br>
